news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation's records 339% increase in regularization fee in FY22
news.para: The figures for the past four fiscals show that collection of regularisation fee rose steadily save for the pandemic-affected 2020-21 when it went below Rs 1 crore and recorded Rs 68 lakh.

news.title: Pune civic body extends deadline for Gunthewari proposal till June 30
news.para: “All valid proposals which can be regularised under this scheme will be entertained. Additional time has been given so that more and more citizens can benefit from this scheme,” said Vikram Kumar, administrator, PMC.

news.title: Cidco launches mega scheme for plots, shops in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Under the scheme, tenements of various housing projects for MIG and HIG, commercial shops, and plots for residential, commercial, and social purposes, will be made available for sale.

news.title: New Delhi Municipal Council collects Rs 942.3 crore from property tax in FY22
news.para: It claimed that it has achieved the highest ever collection of property tax and said it has maintained a continuous streak for the last few years as a financially well governed municipal organisation.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir looks to complete 54,000 houses under PMAY-G in 2022-23
news.para: ​​It is also planning to provide internet connectivity to all gram panchayats, besides constructing or renovating 700 panchayat ghars across the Union territory during the current financial year, he said.

news.title: Asian Paints' new acquisitions unlikely to add colour to its business soon
news.para: Nine years ago, the decorative paints market leader made an entry into modular kitchens through acquisition of Sleek Kitchen and a year later into bathroom fittings through the buyout of Ess Ess bath fittings. However, these businesses contributed only 2.5% to the company's top line for the nine months ended December 2021.

news.title: Restore creditworthiness of buyers in stalled projects: Delhi HC
news.para: Delhi high court has directed the banks to convey to CIBIL to restore the creditworthiness of homebuyers who stopped paying EMIs for incomplete projects.

news.title: Noida: Waiting eight years for flats, Wave Megacity buyers hit the streets
news.para: The protesters are among the 480 buyers – out of a total of 780 flats -- whose investments are stuck in the project that includes residential and commercial spaces in Sector 25A and Sector 32.

news.title: Mumbai: Builders made to apologise for noise pollution due to construction
news.para: Police commissioner Sanjay Pandey has repeatedly warned, through his social media posts, that developers need to adhere to rules. Construction activity is permitted between 6am and 10pm and the maximum decibel limit is 65 in residential areas.

news.title: HDFC Capital, L&T Realty in talks to set up Rs 4,000-crore investment, development platform
news.para: The joint platform to be structured as an Alternative Investment Fund (AIF) and will invest in mid-market residential projects across the country.

news.title: Gurugram: Road is not ready after four years, residents protest
news.para: The protesters pointed out that in 2018, the GMDA allotted a tender for building a 3.3km-long master road, along with drains, for Rs 18.21 crore.

news.title: Jhabua overshoots revenue target through property registration by 100%
news.para: Based on a rise in the real-estate sector of Jhabua after the tribal-dominated district generated revenue of Rs 19.69 Crore in 2019-20 and Rs 26.94 Crore through registration of properties, the state government had set a target of Rs 24 Crore in 2021-22.

news.title: South Delhi civic body's property tax mop-up at an all-time high of Rs 1,075 crore
news.para: SDMC commissioner Gyanesh Bharti credited the success to the efforts of officials concerned who extended all possible help to the taxpayers and made them understand the need of making the payment before the deadline.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram civic body collects property tax of Rs 88 crore in FY22
news.para: While it fell short of the target of Rs 100 crore, the corporation recorded around 17% increase in property tax collection when compared to the previous year.

news.title: Date for filing property tax extended in urban bodies of Chhattisgarh
news.para: Citizens will now be able to pay property tax in urban bodies till April 15. According to the order issued, the last date for payment of property tax and filing returns in urban bodies was fixed till March 31.
